# TypeScript Standards

## Strict Mode

- `strict: true` in all `tsconfig.json` files. No exceptions.
- Never use `any`. Use `unknown` + type narrowing, generics, or explicit union types.
- Never use `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error` without a comment explaining why and a tracking issue.

## Naming

- Files: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g., `note-repository.ts`, `cognitive-state.ts`)
- Interfaces/Types: `PascalCase` (e.g., `NoteRepository`, `CognitiveState`)
- Functions/Variables: `camelCase`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` only for true compile-time constants
- Enums: Prefer union types (`type Status = 'open' | 'done'`) over TypeScript enums

## Domain Models

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Interface + factory function
interface Note {
  id: ULID
  title: string
  body: string
  createdAt: DateTime
}

function createNote(params: CreateNoteParams): Note {
  return { id: generateId(), ...params, createdAt: now() }
}

// ❌ BAD: Class with mixed concerns
class Note {
  constructor(private db: Database) {}
  async save() { /* ... */ }
}
```

## Imports

- Use explicit named imports. No wildcard `import *` except for re-exports from barrel files.
- Barrel files (`index.ts`) only at package boundaries. No barrel files inside feature modules.

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Result type for expected failures
async function findNote(id: ULID): Promise<Result<Note, NotFoundError>> {
  const note = await repo.findById(id)
  if (!note) return { ok: false, error: new NotFoundError(id) }
  return { ok: true, value: note }
}

// ❌ BAD: Throwing for expected cases
async function findNote(id: ULID): Promise<Note> {
  const note = await repo.findById(id)
  if (!note) throw new Error('Not found')
  return note
}
```
